captions.text: What up you fucking offerings from hell. Stop jacking off cause it's time for Group E.
Switzerland
Located in central Europe, Switzerland is one of the countries with best quality of life.
The Swiss Alps is where the bourgeois from around the world like to go skiing,
and it's in their bank accounts that Maluf and a bunch of other shifty politicians
stash the dirty money that they stole from us, stupid gullible Brazilians.
Switzerland's flag looks like the universal hospital symbol.
Valdívia, Fred and Renato Augusto like that.
Switzerland never played well enough to be first in their group,
but since the Fifa headquarters are in Zurich, the hometown of Joseph Blatter, Switzerland is ranked 8th in the world.
The squad defense sometimes resembles a Swiss cheese -- full of holes.
And sometimes a Swiss army knife -- cutting down the opposition with their tools.
Let's go to the highlights.
The defenders Fabian Schar, Philippe Senderos e Tupac Shakur.
And the star of the squad, the attacking midfielder of Bayern Munich, Shaqiri, the heterosexual D'alessandro from the first world.
Ecuador
Ecuador is a South American country stuck between Colombia and Peru.
Coincidentally, Ecuador is where the line that cuts the earth in half is located.
But since the Colombians are their neighbors, the line is gone.
Another coincidence is that in Ecuador the climate is equatorial.
And in the word "Ecuador" we have cu (ass) and dor (pain).
Ecuador greatest glory in soccer wasn't winning the Libertadores Championship of 2008, with LDU, in Maracanã.
Their greatest achievement was not losing the title to Fluminense in court.
The highlights of the Equatorian squad are:
The midfielder Milton Nascimento and Paulinho, from Tottenham.
As well as Vióla and the star Caicedo.
Honduras
Honduras is a Caribbean country that lives off tourism.
And that's exactly what they're going to do in Brazil during the cup.
It's the kind of squad that only takes up space on earth.
Even so, the Honduran squad have already rubbed their dicks in Brazil's face.
It was in the 2001 America Championship, where Brazil had the ability to lose by 2x0 and be eliminated.
Guess who was the Brazilian coach during this embarrassment? Ask Murtosa.
Hondura's jersey is the ugliest of this Cup,
made by the renowned supplier Joma and with this ridiculous giant H symbol,
the jersey looks like a bell boy uniform, that dude that carries your luggage at shitty hotels.
Hondura's squad is so shitty that the coach called a player that doesn't even have a club.
It's that dude, the midfielder Jorge Claros.
And the highlight of the team, Jerry Bengtson, plays in some US team.
Now on to a real squad.
France
France is the cockiest European country.
Everybody is snobby there, wearing scarves, berets, and speak with puckered lips.
The world's best perfumes are French.
It must be because the Françoise don't shower and stink like hell.
Besides B.O., don't be scared if you hook up with a cute French chick and her armpits are hairier than yours.
France is the crib of Napoleon Bonaparte, Voltaire, Illuminism,
freedom, equality, fraternity, Rousseau, Molier, Sartre, Monet, Matisse,
Gauguin, Rodin, Truffaut, Godard, Edith Piaf, Jordi, Platini, Daft Punk,
but in Brazil we only know French bread.
France was almost left out of the World Cup, they only classified in their second chance, with an off side goal.
The best French player ever is not French, he's Algerian.
France only won one Cup, while hosting, because Ronaldo had a convulsion before the finals.
Even so, Brazil is their bitch. Mother of God.
The highlights of La Bleu are:
The defender Varane, from Real Madrid.
And this big guy whom I'm embarrassed to say the name Mamadou Sakho (ball sucker).
The attacking duo Karim Benzema, skinny Mil Grau.
And Franck Ribéry, the hunchback of Notre-Dame after an accident.
If you're still here is because you have nothing else to do, stupid bum.
So stay tuned to Desimpedidos because next week is Argentina, Bosnia, Iran and Nigeria's turn.
